message.content: Since Jenny ate $20\%$ of the jellybeans each day, the fraction remaining at the end of each day is $1-20\%=1-\frac{1}{5}=\frac{4}{5}$ of the fraction remaining the previous day.  Thus, if the number of jellybeans is $x$ at the beginning of the second day, we have $\frac{4}{5}\cdot\frac{4}{5}\cdot x=32$, so $\frac{16}{25}\cdot x=32$ and $x=\boxed{50}$.
